ild\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"How to Create a Style Guide for Your WordPress Website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://theme-fusion.com/how-to-create-a-style-guide-for-your-wordpress-website/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"https://theme-fusion.com/how-to-create-a-style-guide-for-your-wordpress-website/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 16 Dec 2019 16:34:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Design\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Beginners Guide\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Web Design\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Branding\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://theme-fusion.com/?p=678347\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:622:\"<p>As a business, you likely want users to share your brand with others and get excited about using your products. However, managing a brand can be tough, especially online. This can be because web content can be so easily captured, altered, and re-shared. This is where style guides come in! A style guide serves as [...]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theme-fusion.com/how-to-create-a-style-guide-for-your-wordpress-website/\">How to Create a Style Guide for Your WordPress Website</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theme-fusion.com\">ThemeFusion | Professional Website Tools</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"John Hughes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25313:\"<div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-1 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\"  style=\'background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;\'><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row \"><div  class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion_builder_column_1_1 fusion-builder-column-1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last 1_1\"  style=\'margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\'>\n					<div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper\" style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;\"   data-bg-url=\"\">\n						<div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>As a business, you likely want users to share your brand with others and get excited about using your products. However, managing a brand can be tough, especially online. This can be because web content can be so easily captured, altered, and re-shared. This is where style guides come in!</p>\n<p>A style guide serves as protection for all the brand elements youve worked hard to establish for business and <a href=\"http://bit.ly/2l3jd8A\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">online presence</a>. Essentially, style guides create a set of rules that endeavor to keep anyone using your branding in line with your standards.</p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll take a look at how style guides can benefit your brand. We&#8217;ll also discuss what to include in a guide and how to create one. Additionally, well share resources like a <a href=\"https://looka.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">logo generator</a> and explore how they can help with your style guide. Let&#8217;s get started!</p>\n</div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:30px;\"></div><style type=\"text/css\"></style><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-1 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-two\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:20px;\"><h2 class=\"title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">How a Style Guide Can Benefit Your Brand (And What It Should Cover)</h2></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>Typically, style guides are designed to serve two purposes. Companies create these guides to not only help train internal staff but also to establish the rules for using their brand in the public sphere. These guides provide specific standards for how logos and images representing the company can be used. This might include fonts and other styles, along with clear statements of when to never do something.</p>\n<p>Lets take a look at an example to get a better feel for the public face of a style guide. <a href=\"https://www.spotify.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Spotify</a> has a self-explanatory and in-depth <a href=\"https://developer.spotify.com/branding-guidelines/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">online guide</a>:</p>\n</div><div class=\"imageframe-liftup\"><span style=\"border:1px solid #e0dede;\" class=\"fusion-imageframe imageframe-none imageframe-1\"><a href=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-logo-misuse-compressor.png\" class=\"fusion-lightbox\" data-rel=\"iLightbox[dc6516dfee69d8265cd]\" data-title=\"Spotify Logo Misuse\" title=\"Spotify Logo Misuse\"><img src=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-logo-misuse-compressor.png\" data-orig-src=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-logo-misuse-compressor.png\" width=\"2258\" height=\"1772\" alt=\"Spotify Logo Misuse\" class=\"lazyload img-responsive wp-image-681428\" srcset=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%27http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%27%20width%3D%272258%27%20height%3D%271772%27%20viewBox%3D%270%200%202258%201772%27%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%272258%27%20height%3D%2731772%27%20fill-opacity%3D%220%22%2F%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E\" data-srcset=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-logo-misuse-compressor-200x157.png 200w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-logo-misuse-compressor-400x314.png 400w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-logo-misuse-compressor-600x471.png 600w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-logo-misuse-compressor-800x628.png 800w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-logo-misuse-compressor-1200x942.png 1200w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-logo-misuse-compressor.png 2258w\" data-sizes=\"auto\" data-orig-sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 2258px\" /></a></span></div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:30px;\"></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>Rather than being punitive about misuse, Spotify&#8217;s style guide actually invites users to share their brand and gives them the tools with which to do it correctly. This includes downloadable logos.</p>\n<p>Another example that shows how style guides can be as unique as the business they represent is <a href=\"https://www.urbanoutfitters.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Urban Outfitters</a>. The trendy clothing brand has a <a href=\"https://issuu.com/themarkit/docs/urban_outfitters_brand_book_final_p_d1cb1321abd5a6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">style guide</a> that fits the exact look and feel of their clothing:</p>\n</div><span style=\"border:1px solid #e0dede;\" class=\"fusion-imageframe imageframe-none imageframe-2 hover-type-none\"><img src=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook.jpg\" data-orig-src=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook.jpg\" width=\"1497\" height=\"1058\" alt=\"Urban Outfitter&#x27;s Brand Book\" title=\"Urban Outfitter&#8217;s Brand Book\" class=\"lazyload img-responsive wp-image-681430\" srcset=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%27http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%27%20width%3D%271497%27%20height%3D%271058%27%20viewBox%3D%270%200%201497%201058%27%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%271497%27%20height%3D%2731058%27%20fill-opacity%3D%220%22%2F%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E\" data-srcset=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-200x141.jpg 200w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-400x283.jpg 400w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-600x424.jpg 600w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-800x565.jpg 800w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-1200x848.jpg 1200w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook.jpg 1497w\" data-sizes=\"auto\" data-orig-sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 1497px\" /></span><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:30px;\"></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>While this guide may look quite different from Spotify&#8217;s, they both have some commonalities. Both guides include universally essential topics in their content.</p>\n<p>To create a comprehensive and functional document, you might want to consider including:</p>\n</div><ul class=\"fusion-checklist fusion-checklist-1\" style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:27.2px;\"><li class=\"fusion-li-item\"><span style=\"height:27.2px;width:27.2px;margin-right:11.2px;\" class=\"icon-wrapper circle-no\"><i class=\"fusion-li-icon fa-angle-right fas\" style=\"color:#5e5e5e;\"></i></span><div class=\"fusion-li-item-content\" style=\"margin-left:38.4px;\">\n<p><strong>A brand statement</strong>. This sets the mood for your style and brand. It can help get everyone on the same page as well as tell the story of the company.</p>\n</div></li><li class=\"fusion-li-item\"><span style=\"height:27.2px;width:27.2px;margin-right:11.2px;\" class=\"icon-wrapper circle-no\"><i class=\"fusion-li-icon fa-angle-right fas\" style=\"color:#5e5e5e;\"></i></span><div class=\"fusion-li-item-content\" style=\"margin-left:38.4px;\">\n<p><strong>Logos</strong>. A logo is the face of your brand. If you dont have one, you can <a href=\"https://looka.com/logo-maker/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">use a logo maker</a> which can often provide different file types for various uses on your website. You might even want to provide a download on your site, to ensure that the correct version is being shared.</p>\n</div></li><li class=\"fusion-li-item\"><span style=\"height:27.2px;width:27.2px;margin-right:11.2px;\" class=\"icon-wrapper circle-no\"><i class=\"fusion-li-icon fa-angle-right fas\" style=\"color:#5e5e5e;\"></i></span><div class=\"fusion-li-item-content\" style=\"margin-left:38.4px;\">\n<p><strong>Style components</strong>. This includes anything from line spacing, fonts, colors, grid spacing, and more. For example, you want to provide all the <a href=\"https://hackernoon.com/hex-colors-how-do-they-work-d8cb935ac0f\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">color codes</a> and values for web and print use.</p>\n</div></li><li class=\"fusion-li-item\"><span style=\"height:27.2px;width:27.2px;margin-right:11.2px;\" class=\"icon-wrapper circle-no\"><i class=\"fusion-li-icon fa-angle-right fas\" style=\"color:#5e5e5e;\"></i></span><div class=\"fusion-li-item-content\" style=\"margin-left:38.4px;\">\n<p><strong>Copy editing rules</strong>. You can use this section to further emphasize the tone any written copy should convey. This is also where you can specify any unusual spellings or style preferences.</p>\n</div></li><li class=\"fusion-li-item\"><span style=\"height:27.2px;width:27.2px;margin-right:11.2px;\" class=\"icon-wrapper circle-no\"><i class=\"fusion-li-icon fa-angle-right fas\" style=\"color:#5e5e5e;\"></i></span><div class=\"fusion-li-item-content\" style=\"margin-left:38.4px;\">\n<p><strong>Image requirements and rules</strong>. This is another section where you should explicitly state size and quality requirements. This can be for user-generated images, and also regarding the use of your copyrighted image content.</p>\n</div></li></ul><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:10px;\"></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>This may seem a lot  and it can be  but the more you include, the better others can use your brand assets to spread the word.</p>\n</div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:30px;\"></div><style type=\"text/css\"></style><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-2 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-two\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:20px;\"><h2 class=\"title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">How to Create a Style Guide for Your WordPress Website (In 4 Steps)</h2></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>Now you have a good idea of what a style guide might need to contain, let&#8217;s take a look at four steps you can use to create one. We&#8217;ll begin by looking at what you already do to assert your stylistic requirements.</p>\n</div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:20px;\"></div><style type=\"text/css\"></style><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-3 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:20px;\"><h3 class=\"title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Step 1: Review Your Current Style Practices</h3></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>If you already have an established brand, auditing your content can be helpful. This means you&#8217;ll review your existing content and document your existing practices.</p>\n<p>You might want to start with document structures. Take a look at whether you&#8217;re consistently using heading sizes and fonts throughout your content, although it&#8217;s up to you whether you make changes now, or in a specific design session in the future.</p>\n<p>When it comes to your &#8216;base,&#8217; you can either begin to curate a list of existing practices and use them to develop your style guide or establish some changes that will be codified in the style guide.</p>\n</div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:20px;\"></div><style type=\"text/css\"></style><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-4 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:20px;\"><h3 class=\"title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Step 2: Establish and Define Your Brand&#8217;s Voice</h3></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>You can tackle this step in several ways. Most guides include a mission statement or vision at the start of the guide. Ultimately, you can define the brand&#8217;s voice by telling your company&#8217;s story. For example, lets look at <a href=\"https://issuu.com/themarkit/docs/urban_outfitters_brand_book_final_p_d1cb1321abd5a6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Urban Outfitter&#8217;s guide</a> again. Right off the bat, they provide a section called &#8216;Our Story&#8217; that sets the tone for their style:</p>\n</div><span style=\"border:1px solid #e0dede;\" class=\"fusion-imageframe imageframe-none imageframe-3 hover-type-none\"><img src=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-2-compressor.jpg\" data-orig-src=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-2-compressor.jpg\" width=\"1802\" height=\"634\" alt=\"Urban Outfitters Brand Book\" title=\"Urban Outfitters Brand Book\" class=\"lazyload img-responsive wp-image-681439\" srcset=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%27http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%27%20width%3D%271802%27%20height%3D%27634%27%20viewBox%3D%270%200%201802%20634%27%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%271802%27%20height%3D%273634%27%20fill-opacity%3D%220%22%2F%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E\" data-srcset=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-2-compressor-200x70.jpg 200w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-2-compressor-400x141.jpg 400w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-2-compressor-600x211.jpg 600w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-2-compressor-800x281.jpg 800w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-2-compressor-1200x422.jpg 1200w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/urban-outfitters-brandbook-2-compressor.jpg 1802w\" data-sizes=\"auto\" data-orig-sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 1802px\" /></span><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:30px;\"></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>This is where you want to establish what the brand represents, so it&#8217;s best not to leave it to chance. Aside from explicitly stating it, you can also link to examples that showcase your brand&#8217;s voice.</p>\n</div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:20px;\"></div><style type=\"text/css\"></style><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-5 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:20px;\"><h3 class=\"title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Step 3: Create Your Guide Using Your Established Style Rules</h3></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>One of the best ways to establish consistency straight away is to make sure your guide is created by following the same guidelines within. This is a great way to demonstrate your style in context. For example, <a href=\"https://developer.spotify.com/branding-guidelines/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Spotify explicitly shares</a> its color palette, which contains only three colors:</p>\n</div><div class=\"imageframe-liftup\"><span style=\"border:1px solid #e0dede;\" class=\"fusion-imageframe imageframe-none imageframe-4\"><a href=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-brand-color-rules-compressor.jpg\" class=\"fusion-lightbox\" data-rel=\"iLightbox[339697289ff8d88c164]\" data-title=\"Spotify Brand Color Rules\" title=\"Spotify Brand Color Rules\"><img src=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-brand-color-rules-compressor.jpg\" data-orig-src=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-brand-color-rules-compressor.jpg\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1498\" alt=\"Spotify Brand Color Rules\" class=\"lazyload img-responsive wp-image-681440\" srcset=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%27http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%27%20width%3D%271800%27%20height%3D%271498%27%20viewBox%3D%270%200%201800%201498%27%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%271800%27%20height%3D%2731498%27%20fill-opacity%3D%220%22%2F%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E\" data-srcset=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-brand-color-rules-compressor-200x166.jpg 200w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-brand-color-rules-compressor-400x333.jpg 400w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-brand-color-rules-compressor-600x499.jpg 600w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-brand-color-rules-compressor-800x666.jpg 800w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-brand-color-rules-compressor-1200x999.jpg 1200w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/spotify-brand-color-rules-compressor.jpg 1800w\" data-sizes=\"auto\" data-orig-sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 1800px\" /></a></span></div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:30px;\"></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>If Spotify used colors to create their style guide that did not match the green, white, and black required by the guide, it might cause confusion.</p>\n</div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:20px;\"></div><style type=\"text/css\"></style><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-6 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:20px;\"><h3 class=\"title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Step 4: Gather User Feedback and Publish Your Style Guide Online</h3></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>Ultimately, the decisions you make for your style guide are at your discretion. However, you might be able to create a more productive and more functional document if you gather input from others who may be impacted by it. This is an excellent time to share the style guide solely to get some feedback. You can then iterate until you&#8217;re happy.</p>\n<p>Once you have your guide together, reviewed, and approved, you&#8217;ll want to decide where to publish it. Many larger entities, like Twitter, have their brand resources easily <a href=\"https://about.twitter.com/en_us/company/brand-resources.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">located on their site</a>:</p>\n</div><span style=\"border:1px solid #e0dede;\" class=\"fusion-imageframe imageframe-none imageframe-5 hover-type-none\"><img src=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/twitter-brand-resources-compressor.jpg\" data-orig-src=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/twitter-brand-resources-compressor.jpg\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1439\" alt=\"Twitter Brand Resources\" title=\"Twitter Brand Resources\" class=\"lazyload img-responsive wp-image-681446\" srcset=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%27http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%27%20width%3D%271800%27%20height%3D%271439%27%20viewBox%3D%270%200%201800%201439%27%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%271800%27%20height%3D%2731439%27%20fill-opacity%3D%220%22%2F%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E\" data-srcset=\"https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/twitter-brand-resources-compressor-200x160.jpg 200w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/twitter-brand-resources-compressor-400x320.jpg 400w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/twitter-brand-resources-compressor-600x480.jpg 600w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/twitter-brand-resources-compressor-800x640.jpg 800w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/twitter-brand-resources-compressor-1200x959.jpg 1200w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/twitter-brand-resources-compressor.jpg 1800w\" data-sizes=\"auto\" data-orig-sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 1800px\" /></span><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:30px;\"></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>If you&#8217;re using a Content Management System (CMS) such as <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WordPress</a>, you can leverage the platform to create a dynamic and engaging presentation of the content by utilizing the advanced design flexibility <a href=\"http://bit.ly/2l3jd8A\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Avada</a> WordPress theme!</p>\n</div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:30px;\"></div><style type=\"text/css\"></style><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-7 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-two\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:20px;\"><h2 class=\"title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Summary</h2></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>Creating a style guide for your website can have a significant Return on Investment (ROI) for your brand. The time it takes to create a guide means anyone working on your website will have a transparent approach, and a well-defined set of rules to follow.</p>\n<p>To get started on your website style guide, keep these four steps in mind:</p>\n</div><ul class=\"fusion-checklist fusion-checklist-2\" style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:27.2px;\"><li class=\"fusion-li-item\"><span style=\"height:27.2px;width:27.2px;margin-right:11.2px;\" class=\"icon-wrapper circle-no\"><i class=\"fusion-li-icon fa-angle-right fas\" style=\"color:#5e5e5e;\"></i></span><div class=\"fusion-li-item-content\" style=\"margin-left:38.4px;\">Review the styles you currently use.</div></li><li class=\"fusion-li-item\"><span style=\"height:27.2px;width:27.2px;margin-right:11.2px;\" class=\"icon-wrapper circle-no\"><i class=\"fusion-li-icon fa-angle-right fas\" style=\"color:#5e5e5e;\"></i></span><div class=\"fusion-li-item-content\" style=\"margin-left:38.4px;\">Establish your brand&#8217;s voice.</div></li><li class=\"fusion-li-item\"><span style=\"height:27.2px;width:27.2px;margin-right:11.2px;\" class=\"icon-wrapper circle-no\"><i class=\"fusion-li-icon fa-angle-right fas\" style=\"color:#5e5e5e;\"></i></span><div class=\"fusion-li-item-content\" style=\"margin-left:38.4px;\">Create your guide using your own brand standards.</div></li><li class=\"fusion-li-item\"><span style=\"height:27.2px;width:27.2px;margin-right:11.2px;\" class=\"icon-wrapper circle-no\"><i class=\"fusion-li-icon fa-angle-right fas\" style=\"color:#5e5e5e;\"></i></span><div class=\"fusion-li-item-content\" style=\"margin-left:38.4px;\">Gather feedback and publish your guide online.</div></li></ul><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:10px;\"></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p>Do you have any questions about style guide creation? Share your thoughts with us in the comments section below!</p>\n</div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"></div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep sep-none\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:;margin-bottom:30px;\"></div><div class=\"fusion-text\"><p><a style=\"background-color: black; color: white; text-decoration: none; padding: 